      </div>
      <div class="rbp-nbn-faq">
        <details open><summary>How do I check if Business NBN is available at my address?</summary><div>Use the availability checker on the Business NBN signup page. Live serviceability will later connect to the app-proxy endpoint.</div></details>
        <details><summary>Can I choose a 10-payment option?</summary><div>Some plans may support a 10-payment option. Final payment options depend on the selected plan and commercial approval.</div></details>
        <details><summary>Is a static IP available?</summary><div>Static IP availability is plan-dependent. Some plans may include it, while others may offer it as an option.</div></details>
        <details><summary>How long does provisioning take?</summary><div>Provisioning timeframes depend on serviceability, technology type, order completeness, carrier requirements and installation needs.</div></details>
        <details><summary>Can I upgrade later?</summary><div>Upgrade options may be available depending on serviceability, selected plan, contract/payment option and business requirements.</div></details>
        <details><summary>What happens if my address is not serviceable?</summary><div>If availability cannot be confirmed, the order should move to manual review so alternative options or next steps can be assessed.</div></details>
